    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1036"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1036">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00 TA/3–353</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1036fn1">Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName> drafted this memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-16">March 16,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may be interested in the final paragraph of a recent cable from <persName
                        corresp="#p_BCB1">Chester Bowles</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d1036fn2">See <ref target="#d1035fn2">footnote 2, <hi
                                rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> on Indian aid— <pb facs="0644" n="1694" xml:id="pg_1694"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Only rational basis reducing aid request is reject our political
                            estimate (one word here garbled, correction to follow)<note n="3"
                                xml:id="d1036fn3">The garbled word in New Delhi telegram 3455, Mar.
                                2, was “India’s”.</note> vital importance and danger of failure.
                            This responsibility must be clearly and openly assumed in Washington. In
                            my considered opinion it would be prelude to disaster.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am actually recommending a reduction from a projected $200,000,000 to
                        $140,000,000.<note n="4" xml:id="d1036fn4">According to a memorandum dated
                        Nov. 9, 1953 from <persName corresp="#p_SH2">Harold E. Stassen</persName>,
                        the Director of the Foreign Operations Administration, to Secretary of State
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, a total of $89,100,000
                        eventually was made available by Congress for technical assistance and
                        economic aid to India in <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1954 (791.5
                            <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/11–953).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
